+# PR-214 Remediation Report
+
+## Thread Classification
+
+- `T-214-01`: actionable
+- `T-214-02`: duplicate of `T-214-01`
+- `T-214-03`: obsolete
+- `T-214-04`: actionable
+- `T-214-05`: actionable
+
+Classification source of truth: `.github/review_export/pr_214_threads.json`
+
+## Changes Applied
+
+### `src/policy/approval_router.py`
+
+- `build_policy_preview(...)` now normalizes the incoming approval state before calling `build_preview_payload(...)`.
+
+### `src/policy/preview.py`
+
+- The fallback `preview_enabled=False` payload now preserves:
+  - `approval_state`
+  - `requires_human_review`
+- This keeps fallback behavior aligned with the live preview payload for human-review routing.
+
+### `tests/test_preview.py`
+
+- Added a regression test covering:
+  - `approval_state="manual_review"`
+  - `preview_enabled=False`
+  - expected normalized fallback values:
+    - `approval_state="human_review_required"`
+    - `requires_human_review=True`
+
+### `docs/approval_policy.md`
+
+- Updated the fallback response example to show the corrected payload fields.
+- Replaced the stale note about pending review follow-up with the current behavior.
+
+## Verification
+
+Command run:
+
+```bash
+python3 -m unittest tests.test_preview tests.test_approval_router
+```
+
+Result:
+
+- `5` tests run
+- `OK`
+
+## Notes
+
+- `artifacts/review/thread_digest.md` was treated as a stale hint only and was not used as the classification authority.
+- No legacy preview behavior was restored or introduced.
+- No changes were made to the prohibited files or directories listed in `AGENTS.md`.
