+T-214-01
+
+Implemented the fallback payload fix in `src/policy/preview.py` so the preview-unavailable response now preserves `approval_state` and `requires_human_review`. The router now normalizes `manual_review` to `human_review_required` before building the payload, so the reopened fallback case keeps the expected human-review fields.
+
+T-214-02
+
+Classified as duplicate of `T-214-01`. This thread reports the same reopened fallback payload regression, so no separate code change was applied.
+
+T-214-03
+
+Classified as obsolete. The suggestion points at an outdated diff hunk and asks to revive legacy behavior on the current branch, so it was intentionally not applied.
+
+T-214-04
+
+Added a writable regression in `tests/test_preview.py` that exercises `build_policy_preview(..., preview_enabled=False, approval_state="manual_review", ...)` and asserts the fallback payload keeps `approval_state="human_review_required"` with `requires_human_review=True`.
+
+T-214-05
+
+Updated `docs/approval_policy.md` so the fallback example now includes `approval_state: "human_review_required"` and `requires_human_review: true`, matching the corrected fallback payload.
